In Apache Spark, a join combines two DataFrames based on a common key (horizontally), whereas a union combines two DataFrames by stacking rows (vertically) without any matching condition.”

🔹 Join
Explanation

“Join merges columns from two DataFrames using a key.”

Code
df1.join(df2, "id", "inner").show()

Union
Explanation

“Union combines rows of two DataFrames with the same schema.”

Code
df1.union(df2).show()
